    <item>
      <title>Embracing Responsibility for Change</title>
      <link>/wiaposts/Embracing-Responsibility-for-Change/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 01 Oct 2024 08:33:00 +0530</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>/wiaposts/Embracing-Responsibility-for-Change/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;/assets/images/wiapost/5266-Embracing-Responsibility-for-Change.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Embracing Responsibility for Change&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Embracing Responsibility for Change 
    &lt;div id=&#34;embracing-responsibility-for-change&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#embracing-responsibility-for-change&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When we say nowadays the surrounding is corrupt,&lt;br&gt;
we need to ask: where does this surrounding start?&lt;br&gt;
At my heart, skin, bedroom, flat, apartment, district, state, etc.?&lt;br&gt;
We need to ask ourselves how we reached the conclusion&lt;br&gt;
that it was not corrupt earlier.&lt;br&gt;
We need to ask ourselves what we are doing,&lt;br&gt;
apart from adding to that corruption at our own level.&lt;br&gt;
If I am not part of the solution,&lt;br&gt;
then there is a high chance I am part of the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Are you not Nature?</title>
      <link>/wiaposts/are-you-not-nature/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 04 Jul 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>/wiaposts/are-you-not-nature/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;/assets/images/wiapost/5192-Are-You-Not-Nature.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Are you not Nature?&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Are you not Nature? 
    &lt;div id=&#34;are-you-not-nature&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#are-you-not-nature&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If a man thinks he has done something against Mother Nature  &lt;br&gt;
that is why nature is punishing him or going to punish him then  &lt;br&gt;
he forgets that he himself is part of the parcel of nature.  &lt;br&gt;
There is no other separate nature away from your own bodily existence.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>About Responsibility</title>
      <link>/wiaposts/about-responsibility/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 20 Mar 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>/wiaposts/about-responsibility/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;/assets/images/wiapost/5013-About-Responsibility.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;About Responsibility&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;About Responsibility 
    &lt;div id=&#34;about-responsibility&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#about-responsibility&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibility is a Noun. But it takes birth from a verb “ability”.  &lt;br&gt;
The ability to respond is called responsibility&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Who is that living being who cannot respond?  &lt;br&gt;
Only dead cannot respond!  &lt;br&gt;
The question is about choice.  &lt;br&gt;
To something, we want to respond to some others not.  &lt;br&gt;
But that is called freedom.  &lt;br&gt;
Who is that wise person who wants to renounce his freedom?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
